### `ReplaySessionMetadata`

Describes a recorded session for manifest indexing.

```typescript
interface ReplaySessionMetadata {
  demoType: string;        // Category identifier
  sessionId: string;        // Unique session identifier
  modes: string[];         // Active agent modes
  models: string[];         // Models used
  capturedAt: number;      // Unix timestamp (ms)
  tokenCount: number;       // Estimated total tokens
  eventCount: number;      // Total events
  description: string;     // Human-readable description
}
```

### `ReplaySessionData`

Pre-existing state at session start.

```typescript
interface ReplaySessionData {
  messages: NormalizedMessage[];
  thoughts: NormalizedThought[];
  toolCalls: NormalizedToolCall[];
  sessionId: string;
  cwd: string;
}
```

### `ReplayEvent`

```typescript
interface ReplayEvent {
  envelope: BridgeEnvelope;
  tokenCount: number;
}
```

### `ReplayManifest`

```typescript
interface ReplayManifest {
  demoType: string;
  sessions: ReplaySessionMetadata[];
}
```

### `estimateTokenCount(text: string): number`

Uses Math.ceil(text.length / 4). Suitable for UI display and replay timing.

---

## Replay Controller API

The ReplayController provides a SessionController-compatible interface for driving the Rust bridge in replay mode.

### Construction

```typescript
const controller = new ReplayController({
  bridgeUrl: 'ws://localhost:8765/replay-v2',
  modes: [{ id: 'analyze', name: 'Analyze' }],
  models: [{ id: 'claude-sonnet-4', name: 'Claude Sonnet 4' }],
  requestTimeoutMs: 30000,
});
```

---

## Usage Examples

### Complete Replay Workflow

```typescript
import { ReplayController, createNormalizedState, applySessionUpdate, getMessages } from '@anthropic/acp-chat-core';

const replay = new ReplayController({
  bridgeUrl: 'ws://localhost:8765/replay-v2',
  modes: [
    { id: 'analyze', name: 'Analyze' },
    { id: 'summarize', name: 'Summarize' },
    { id: 'extract', name: 'Extract' },
  ],
  models: [
    { id: 'claude-sonnet-4', name: 'Claude Sonnet 4', provider: 'anthropic' },
    { id: 'gpt-4o', name: 'GPT-4o', provider: 'openai' },
    { id: 'gemini-2.5-pro', name: 'Gemini 2.5 Pro', provider: 'google' },
  ],
});

const state = createNormalizedState();
replay.on('sessionUpdate', (params) => {
  applySessionUpdate(state, params);
  console.log('Messages:', getMessages(state).length);
});

await replay.connect();
await replay.initialize({ name: 'demo-app', version: '1.0.0' });
await replay.createSession('/project', [], 'long-context', 'lc-analysis-001');
await replay.sendPrompt('lc-analysis-001', 'Analyze this codebase');
```

This completes the comprehensive API documentation for the replay module.
